1
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:55,740
=Sugar and Lies=
(A Different Her: The Women's Trilogy)

2
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:59,780
=Episode 9=
=Bubbles in the Sun=

3
00:01:01,070 --> 00:01:01,960
(Keep Love)
Hey there.

4
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:02,880
Today we're diving into

5
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:04,200
a perfect-in-the-moment topic:

6
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:06,520
The last wild fling before marriage.

7
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:09,200
So, Mr. Zhou,

8
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,600
do you see this as human nature

9
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,440
or as showing no respect for marriage?

10
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,480
I just don't know what to do with you.

11
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,760
After this week,

12
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:22,680
forget me.

13
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:30,920
From a psychology perspective,

14
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,360
this is often tied to

15
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,760
tied to pre-wedding anxiety

16
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,480
and pressure about the responsibility

17
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:36,720
brought by marriage and tied to

18
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:38,560
a desire to
hold on to the last freedom.

19
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,800
But...

20
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:42,960
But reality always hits hard.

21
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:44,480
After the rush fades,

22
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,400
it's not just yourself who gets hurt.

23
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,560
Innocent partners and family suffer too.

24
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,280
That's a painful truth to face.

25
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,520
Mr. Zhou must have endured
plenty of heartbreak.

26
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,920
No time like the present.

27
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,200
Tell us your story.

28
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,680
That's not in the script.

29
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:01,400
Love stories don't follow a script.

30
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,800
Take a breath,
ease that pre-wedding anxiety.

31
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,920
Reckless actions

32
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,160
always come with a cost.

33
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,800
Seriously, don't cheat.

34
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,480
Did you hear that?

35
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:10,720
They were talking about you.

36
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,800
Or maybe at someone else.

37
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:19,960
I mean,

38
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,720
did you Gu Ruomai in as a streamer

39
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,280
just to get close to me?

40
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,240
What's the answer you're expecting?

41
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,120
That's exactly my answer.

42
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,200
It doesn't matter.

43
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,280
What matters is

44
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,680
you're right here with me now.

45
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,920
Gu Ruomai can be pretty tough.

46
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:53,280
I remember back then,

47
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,240
she even hit me for your sake.

48
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,700
Chen Aming,

49
00:02:57,700 --> 00:02:59,240
serves you right for treating her

50
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,160
like that!

51
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:02,720
Do you know
how much Ding Daang has done for you?

52
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:17,880
It's on me.

53
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:20,100
Thanks for helping me last time.

54
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,640
Give it a try.

55
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,680
You made it?

56
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,280
Not bad.

57
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,320
I'm no cook.

58
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,620
This is the only dish I can make.

59
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,160
Honestly, I've never had dumplings before.

60
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,000
Your parents never made that?

61
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:05,960
I don't have parents.

62
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,280
What a coincidence, same here.

63
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,760
But at least you've got a sister.

64
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,360
If you like,

65
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,760
she could be your sister too.

66
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:37,540
(Suga Love)

67
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:38,420
(Finance New Wave)

68
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,000
Why is President Hu here again?

69
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,480
He's been here

70
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,000
three afternoons in a row

71
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,280
to read.

72
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,680
Boss isn't around.

73
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,920
He's still here waiting for her.

74
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,400
What a devoted man.

75
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,120
True.

76
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,040
Where do you think the boss is?

77
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,680
Can't reach her through phone.

78
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,120
The engagement ceremony
is only days away.

79
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,920
Guess it's that pre-wedding anxiety

80
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,560
kicking in.

81
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,520
The service is over.

82
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:32,960
Um…

83
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,960
Can we renew the contract?

84
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,920
We agreed to call it even.

85
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,680
I'm not happy with your service.

86
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:43,990
The debt isn't cleared yet.

87
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,880
You're getting engaged.

88
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,840
But didn't you come back

89
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,280
to stop my engagement?

90
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,980
♪Why can't I just let it go♪

91
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,040
Come on, don't tease me.

92
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:03,230
♪But how could they ever know
how good you were to me♪

93
00:06:03,380 --> 00:06:06,460
(A Goodbye Kiss
is good for an emotional closure.)

94
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:09,290
♪As the endless night unfolds♪

95
00:06:09,290 --> 00:06:12,000
♪I toss and turn, can't fall asleep♪

96
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:16,900
♪You keep running through my mind♪

97
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:19,930
♪Nothing matters more than you♪

98
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,470
♪Why♪

99
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,000
Ding Daang.

100
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,840
They're fighting.

101
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,960
Relax, it's fine.

102
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,920
With our boss's EQ,

103
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,160
she's got that situation

104
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,080
under control.

105
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,240
You're right.

106
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,000
But if it were you,

107
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,080
who would you choose?

108
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,560
Honestly,

109
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,960
that's a tough choice.

110
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,040
After all,

111
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,240
they're both good-looking

112
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,880
and both loaded.

113
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,800
Ding Daang.

114
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,740
Where have you been these days?

115
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,080
I want to talk to you properly.

116
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,880
Can you ask the unrelated man to leave?

117
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,560
As you can see,

118
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,640
I cheated.

119
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,240
Let's call off the engagement.

120
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,280
I owe you an apology for this.

121
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,280
Tell me whatever you need.

122
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,040
You're not even trying to hide it.

123
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:31,680
It doesn't bother me.

124
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,880
The ceremony will be held on time.

125
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,960
Do you know what you're saying?

126
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,720
Of course.

127
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,560
I believe in our relationship.

128
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,120
Ding Daang.

129
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,760
Your fiancé...

130
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,440
He's... quite something.

131
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,320
But there are things

132
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,500
which I do mind,

133
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,480
even Ding Daang doesn't.

134
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,440
And who are you to mind?

135
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,080
President Hu.

136
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,720
You really can be cold.

137
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:07,520
Have you already forgotten

138
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,000
Chen...

139
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,240
Miao...

140
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,240
Miao?

141
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,200
Stop talking nonsense.

142
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,040
Miaomiao?

143
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,280
Your sister,

144
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,120
Chen Miaomiao?

145
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,480
President Hu,

146
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,440
I almost believed your nonsense.

147
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,160
While preparing for your engagement,

148
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,400
your were playing

149
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,440
those games of affection with other girls.

150
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,360
What a shame.

151
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:44,840
You picked the wrong person.

152
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,280
Hu Yitong.

153
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,800
What's your relationship with Miaomiao?

154
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,520
Yes.

155
00:08:59,080 --> 00:08:59,920
Miaomiao and I

156
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,880
used to be together.

157
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,600
But we broke up a long time ago.

158
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,400
If you have any proof

159
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,800
that I betrayed Ding Daang,

160
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,400
please bring it out.

161
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,600
Mr. Hu, looks like

162
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,280
you came prepared.

163
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,400
Let me think.

164
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,200
Hotel surveillance.

165
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,040
Date photos.

166
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,120
Transaction records.

167
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,560
I'd guess
these have all been tampered with.

168
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,200
Still,

169
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,200
I could let Ding Daang have a look.

170
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,040
Ding Daang.

171
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:14,990
I admit Chen Miaomiao
came to me a few times.

172
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,520
But I never

173
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,160
crossed any lines with her.

174
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,360
If you don't believe me,

175
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,280
you can ask her yourself.

176
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,560
Ding Daang,

177
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,040
do you believe him?

178
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,600
President Yu,

179
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:40,280
if you're demanding
an explanation for your sister,

180
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,680
you could've come to me directly.

181
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,040
But please don't use Ding Daang.

182
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,240
Yu Kun.

183
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,800
If something really happens to Miaomiao,

184
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:56,820
you should take responsibility.

185
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:59,720
Because the one who's hurt her the most

186
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,760
is you, her brother.

187
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,880
If I'm not mistaken,

188
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:05,980
you planned my so-called chance meeting

189
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,920
with her, didn't you?

190
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,280
You only came to Ding Daang

191
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,440
for your own career, didn't you?

192
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:19,960
Hu Yitong.

193
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,580
I have no idea what you're talking about.

194
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:54,620
♪I forgot this is a movie meant for one♪

195
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:06,380
♪Somehow you're still here,
crying with me♪

196
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,770
♪They say♪

197
00:12:13,180 --> 00:12:21,560
♪Lovers should never hold hands
while watching a sad movie♪

198
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:25,060
♪Some endings cannot be changed♪

199
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:31,230
♪They don't belong in sweet memories♪

200
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:38,370
♪I've already lost you♪

201
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:43,850
♪Thinking of it takes my breath away♪

202
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:50,100
♪The movie ends, so many couples around♪

203
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:54,880
♪Yet none were ever like us♪

204
00:12:55,990 --> 00:13:00,020
♪The past will always pass♪

205
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:07,930
♪If you could still hold me tight
in your arms♪

206
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,650
♪I'd believe
that there are miracles in love♪

207
00:13:12,210 --> 00:13:17,860
♪I'd prove
that I'm still in love with you♪

208
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:23,850
♪I've learned how to cherish
what we had♪

209
00:13:23,850 --> 00:13:30,110
♪But sadly, it's not you♪
